    <stitle>RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700 Models - RADIATOR AND COMPONENT REMOVAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>RADIATOR AND COMPONENT REMOVAL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="7">
            <title>componenT</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Park chassis on a flat level surface. Place transmission in neutral (or park if
                    automatic transmission), set the parking brake, turn off ignition, install wheel chocks and
                    disconnect battery.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the grille and shroud assembly to access the A/C condenser mounting assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1201001">Figure 1, Item 3</hotlnk>) if applicable. This applies to standard grille
                    and shroud configuration.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1201001" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                             scalefitheight="352px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Grille Removal (Standard Grille)</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. GRILLE SHROUD INSERT TABS</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. CROSSBAR GRILLE MOUNTING BRACKETS</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. GRILLE SHROUD</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. LOWER GRILLE MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1201002" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="f1201002.webp" filename="../figg12/g1201002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Fixed Grille Assembly (Remove and Replace)</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. RADIATOR TOP FRAME</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. FIXED GRILLE UPPER MOUNTING BRACKETS</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. GRILLE MOUNTING BRACKET ATTACHMENT BOLTS</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. GRILLE ASSEMBLY MOUNTING SPEED NUTS</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. FIXED GRILLE LOWER MOUNTING BRACKETS</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. GRILLE MOUNTING BRACKET BOLTS</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. GRILLE MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. FIXED GRILLE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fixed grille assembly requires removal of grille from radiator frame assembly. Shroud
                    will tilt with hood.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release the hood latches and tilt hood forward.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support the tilted hood on a padded surface to prevent scratches or damage to the hood
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate and disconnect the chassis hood harness from the radiator frame each side (if
                    applicable) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1201003">Figure 3, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201003" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Harness Connectors (Each Side of Radiator)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CHASSIS HOOD HARNESS CONNECTION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FRAME RAIL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prior to removal of any cooling system components locate radiator drain cock (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1201004">Figure 4, Item 1</hotlnk>). Place tray under radiator to collect coolant
                    from radiator. Open pet cock and drain coolant.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201004" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201004.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Radiator Pet Cock</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PET COCK</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RADIATOR SIDE FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CHARGE AIR COOLER MOUNTING BUSHING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1201005" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Driver Side Splash Panel and Hood Section</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HOOD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DRIVERS SIDE SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate and remove the driver side splash panel mounting screws from hood assembly
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1201005">(Figure 5, Item 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove driver side splash panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate passenger side splash panel mounting brackets (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1201006">Figure 6, Items 2 and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate tabs on splash shield. Push tabs in and lift splash panel in upward direction to
                    remove splash panel from mounting brackets. Mounting tabs must be clear of bracket for removal (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1201006">Figure 6, Items 1 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Passenger Side Splash Panel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. REAR SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING TAB</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. REAR SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FORWARD SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING TAB</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FRONT SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove splash panel. Depending on application, the forward splash panel bracket
                    (passenger side) may require removal (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1201006">Figure 6, Item 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the mounting bolts on the forward splash panel bracket attachment at the frame
                    rail. Loosen bolts and nuts from bracket assembly and remove bracket, as may be required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate charge air cooler hoses and tension spring clamps each side (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1201007">Figure 7, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the tension spring clamps at the charge air cooler port closest to charge air
                    cooler (each side).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the right side charge air cooler connection hose from the engine and charge air
                    cooler port.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect left side charge air cooler hose from charge air cooler. Cap the charge air
                    cooler ports.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove P-clips attachments as may be required.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201007" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Tension Spring Clamp</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TENSION SPRING CLAMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHARGE AIR COOLER CONNECTOR HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CHARGE AIR COOLER PIPES</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
